---
description: Enforce core on-page SEO standards whenever building or editing page markup/content.
globs: **/*.vue, **/*.html
alwaysApply: false
---

- Title tags: unique per page, keyword-relevant, readable, and within practical snippet limits.
- Meta descriptions: unique, specific, human-readable, and value-oriented.
- Canonical: every indexable page must declare a self-referencing absolute canonical URL.
- Heading architecture: exactly one `h1`; align page heading structure with page intent/type.
- Image alt text: descriptive and meaningful; avoid stuffing; decorative images use empty alt.
- Keep page-level SEO checks aligned to page type (homepage, service/product, blog, location).

- 🚩 Duplicate or vague title tags.
- 🚩 Missing/duplicate/thin meta descriptions.
- 🚩 Missing/incorrect canonical tag on indexable page.
- 🚩 Multiple `h1` or misaligned heading structure.
- 🚩 Missing/non-descriptive image alt text on meaningful images.
- 🚩 Page type missing expected SEO-critical elements.

See `.cursor/skills/seo-on-page/SKILL.md` for full reference and checklists.
